INSERT INTO public.question_bank_questions (product_slug, bank_type, category, question, options, correct_answer, explanation, sort_order) VALUES
('platinum-wealth-venture','study','suitability','Which client is most suitable for Platinum Wealth Venture?','["A client who needs most of the money within 2 years","A client with stable surplus cash flow and a medium-to-long-term investment horizon","A client who wants guaranteed yearly returns with no fluctuations","A client whose main need is comprehensive critical illness protection"]'::jsonb,1,'PWV is more suitable for clients who can commit to the 5-year premium term, do not need near-term liquidity, and are comfortable with a market-linked wealth accumulation plan. It is less suitable for clients seeking short-term access, guaranteed yearly returns, or comprehensive protection coverage.',120),
('platinum-wealth-venture','study','suitability','Which client is least suitable for Platinum Wealth Venture?','["A pre-retiree planning future retirement income","A business owner with surplus cash and long-term goals","A client who may need the committed capital for a property purchase in 3 years","A client interested in legacy and wealth transfer planning"]'::jsonb,2,'PWV is generally less suitable for capital likely to be needed in the short term. A client planning to use the money within a few years may face a mismatch between product structure and liquidity needs.',121),
('platinum-wealth-venture','study','suitability','What is the most important suitability check before recommending PWV?','["Whether the client qualifies for the dividend-paying fund","Whether the client can comfortably sustain the 5-year premium commitment without affecting liquidity needs","Whether the client prefers quarterly or annual reviews","Whether the client already has a private banker"]'::jsonb,1,'The most important issue is whether the commitment fits the client''s cash flow and liquidity planning. A strong recommendation should never be driven only by product features or illustrations.',122),
('platinum-wealth-venture','study','suitability','A client says, "I hate seeing my investment value go down at all." What should the advisor conclude?','["PWV is automatically suitable because of its bonuses","The client''s expectations may not fit a market-linked policy","The client only needs a larger premium commitment","The client should choose PWV because of the death benefit"]'::jsonb,1,'Since PWV is an ILP, policy value can fluctuate with markets. If the client cannot accept any fluctuation, the advisor should reassess whether the product is suitable rather than force-fit the case.',123),
('platinum-wealth-venture','study','suitability','Which client objective aligns best with Platinum Wealth Venture?','["Building long-term wealth with possible future income use","Parking emergency funds","Paying for a major expense next year","Replacing a hospital plan"]'::jsonb,0,'PWV is more naturally aligned to long-term wealth accumulation, future retirement income positioning, and legacy planning than to emergency liquidity or medical protection replacement.',124),
('platinum-wealth-venture','study','suitability','A client wants PWV mainly because "the bonuses look attractive." What is the best advisor response?','["Proceed, since bonuses alone justify the case","Recommend the highest possible premium immediately","Clarify the client''s goals, liquidity needs, and time horizon before deciding if the product fits","Focus only on the death benefit instead"]'::jsonb,2,'A product should not be recommended based only on attractive bonuses. A mature advisor checks whether the plan actually fits the client''s broader financial situation and objectives.',125),
('platinum-wealth-venture','study','suitability','A client can afford the minimum annual premium, but only if everything goes perfectly financially. What is the best interpretation?','["The case is clearly suitable","Affordability may be too marginal and needs deeper review","The client should commit now before rates change","The client should add more premium to get better value"]'::jsonb,1,'If affordability depends on nothing going wrong, the plan may not be comfortably sustainable. Advisors should recommend based on resilience, not optimism.',126),
('platinum-wealth-venture','study','suitability','Which statement best reflects proper liquidity planning when considering PWV?','["All spare funds should go into structured plans for discipline","Only money not needed for short-term use or emergencies should be committed to PWV","Emergency funds are unnecessary for affluent clients","The 5-year premium term means liquidity planning is not important"]'::jsonb,1,'Even for affluent clients, emergency and short-term liquidity should usually be kept separate from long-term market-linked plans. This is good advisory practice.',127),
('platinum-wealth-venture','study','suitability','A client wants to use money intended for their child''s school fees in the next 2 to 4 years to fund PWV. What is the best response?','["Proceed because the bonuses should make up for the timing","Explain that near-term education funds generally should not be committed into this type of long-term plan","Recommend a more aggressive fund choice","Suggest topping up later if needed"]'::jsonb,1,'The issue is not only returns but suitability of time horizon. Short-term education money and medium-to-long-term ILP commitments usually serve different purposes.',128),
('platinum-wealth-venture','study','suitability','Which client profile is most likely to need extra caution before recommending PWV?','["A client with stable income and clear long-term goals","A client with irregular cash flow and weak emergency reserves","A client who understands market fluctuations","A client who already has diversified assets"]'::jsonb,1,'Irregular cash flow and poor liquidity are two of the biggest warning signs that the commitment may not be suitable or may need to be sized more conservatively.',129),
('platinum-wealth-venture','study','suitability','When might a fixed deposit or high-yield savings account be more suitable than PWV?','["When the client wants long-term capital growth with market participation","When the client needs high liquidity and low volatility for short-term funds","When the client is focused on legacy planning","When the client wants a Secondary Insured feature"]'::jsonb,1,'PWV is not a cash-management product. Short-term, high-liquidity funds are often better placed in simpler, lower-volatility instruments.',130),
('platinum-wealth-venture','study','suitability','When might PWV be more suitable than directly self-managing a unit trust portfolio?','["When the client values structure, integrated policy benefits, and a defined premium commitment","When the client wants zero product-related charges","When the client only wants short-term tactical investing","When the client wants complete liquidity from the start"]'::jsonb,0,'Some clients value structure, bonuses, death benefit features, and succession-related elements that direct investing does not provide in the same way.',131),
('platinum-wealth-venture','study','compliance','What is the advisor''s primary responsibility when discussing PWV?','["To maximize premium size for better projections","To recommend a solution that is suitable for the client''s needs, budget, and objectives","To focus only on the strongest product features","To avoid discussing risk unless the client asks"]'::jsonb,1,'Suitability comes before sales. A strong advisor aligns the recommendation to the client''s circumstances, rather than pushing the product based on appeal alone.',132),
('platinum-wealth-venture','study','compliance','Which statement is the most appropriate way to describe PWV?','["This is suitable for almost every affluent client.","This can be suitable for the right client if the budget, horizon, and planning objectives fit.","This guarantees retirement income if you hold it long enough.","This is basically a savings account with bonuses."]'::jsonb,1,'This wording is balanced and suitable. It avoids universal claims and does not overpromise outcomes.',133),
('platinum-wealth-venture','study','compliance','Which statement should an advisor avoid?','["PWV is a market-linked plan, so policy value can fluctuate.","We should first check whether this fits your liquidity and long-term goals.","You can safely put all your spare cash here and use it as your emergency reserve too.","The product may play a role in broader retirement or legacy planning."]'::jsonb,2,'That statement encourages poor financial planning and mixes up emergency liquidity with long-term investing.',134),
('platinum-wealth-venture','study','compliance','A client appears enthusiastic about PWV, but clearly has weak cash flow and near-term funding needs. What is the best response?','["Proceed because enthusiasm is the main thing that matters","Slow down and explain why the plan may not be suitable in its current form","Push urgency so the client does not change their mind","Focus on the dividend illustration and ignore the mismatch"]'::jsonb,1,'Enthusiasm is not the same as suitability. A strong advisor is willing to pause or reshape the recommendation when the fit is weak.',135),
('platinum-wealth-venture','study','compliance','A client has several older policies and wants to surrender them to fund PWV. What should the advisor do first?','["Proceed immediately because newer products are usually better","Review surrender implications, guarantees, current values, original objectives, and whether replacement is truly suitable","Focus only on the new dividend projection","Recommend surrendering the weakest-looking policy first without analysis"]'::jsonb,1,'Replacement and restructuring should never be handled casually. Proper comparison is necessary before advising any surrender.',136),
('platinum-wealth-venture','study','compliance','Which of the following is the safest way to present PWV in a healthcare-cost conversation?','["As a medical insurance replacement","As a guaranteed future healthcare funding solution","As an asset-building tool that may support future premium or retirement cash-flow needs, depending on performance and suitability","As a direct way to pay hospital bills through the policy"]'::jsonb,2,'This framing keeps the product in its proper role. It avoids turning PWV into something it is not.',137),
('platinum-wealth-venture','study','compliance','A client asks whether dividends from PWV can be relied on to fully pay future hospitalization premiums. What is the best response?','["Yes, dividends will definitely cover those premiums","No, because dividends are irrelevant to planning","Dividends are not guaranteed, so they can be part of planning scenarios but should not be presented as certain outcomes","Yes, if the client chooses the income fund"]'::jsonb,2,'This is the compliant and realistic response. Income-oriented funds may support planning, but outcomes should not be guaranteed.',138),
('platinum-wealth-venture','study','advisory-skills','Before presenting PWV, which discovery question is most valuable?','["How much can you comfortably commit each year without affecting your emergency fund or short-term needs?","Would you like the highest bonus version first?","Do you want the income fund or growth fund?","Can I show you the illustration before understanding your goals?"]'::jsonb,0,'This question helps the advisor assess affordability and suitability before presenting product details.',139),
('platinum-wealth-venture','study','advisory-skills','Which question best helps determine whether PWV should be positioned as growth, income, or legacy planning?','["What do you want this money to do for you over the next 10 to 20 years?","Do you want quarterly reviews?","Should I compare it to Pro Achiever right away?","Would you prefer PayNow dividends?"]'::jsonb,0,'This question uncovers the client''s objective and guides how the product should be positioned, if at all.',140),
('platinum-wealth-venture','study','advisory-skills','A client already has a private banker, dividend stocks, and multiple insurance policies. What is the best advisory approach?','["Assume PWV should replace everything else","Ignore the existing setup and just show the new illustration","Map what the client already has and identify whether PWV fills any real planning gap","Lead with the lower charge comparison immediately"]'::jsonb,2,'A strong advisor sells into a genuine gap, not just into a wealthy client.',141),
('platinum-wealth-venture','study','advisory-skills','A client says, "I''m interested only if this clearly improves my current financial setup." What is the best response?','["It definitely will, because it''s a newer product.","Let''s first review what you already have and see whether PWV adds anything meaningful.","The bonuses alone prove it is better.","Trust me, that''s why I''m here."]'::jsonb,1,'This is the response of an advisor, not a product pusher. Improvement should be demonstrated, not assumed.',142),
('platinum-wealth-venture','study','advisory-skills','A client says, "I like the dividend angle, but I may not need income immediately." What is the best advisor response?','["Then PWV is not for you.","That can still work — dividends can be reinvested first, then switched to cash later if needed.","You must take dividends in cash from the start.","Income funds only work for retirees."]'::jsonb,1,'This shows flexibility and helps the client understand that the strategy can evolve over time.',143),
('platinum-wealth-venture','study','advisory-skills','A client asks whether PWV should be funded using fresh cash, fixed deposits, or surrendered policies. What is the best response?','["Use old policies first because they usually underperform.","Use fixed deposits first because they are low yield.","We should compare the role, liquidity, and opportunity cost of each funding source before deciding.","It doesn''t matter as long as we start now."]'::jsonb,2,'Source-of-funds is a planning issue. A strong advisor does not reduce it to a simple yield comparison.',144),
('platinum-wealth-venture','study','advisory-skills','What is the clearest sign that an advisor is overselling PWV?','["They explain how bonuses work","They compare charges honestly","They present PWV as the solution before understanding the client''s full financial situation","They ask about retirement goals"]'::jsonb,2,'Premature recommendation is a classic sign of weak advisory process.',145),
('platinum-wealth-venture','study','advisory-skills','Which meeting flow is strongest when introducing PWV to a pre-retiree?','["Lead with the dividend chart immediately","Start with their concerns, audit their current setup, educate through scenarios, then position PWV if suitable","Focus on urgency and close in the first meeting","Spend most of the time attacking their existing products"]'::jsonb,1,'This reflects consultative selling rather than product dumping.',146),
('platinum-wealth-venture','study','closing','A client says, "I like the concept, but I want to review my budget first." What is the best response?','["No problem — let''s review your budget properly and decide on a comfortable amount, if any.","You should start first and think later.","Budget matters less than getting in early.","If you need to think, you''re probably not serious."]'::jsonb,0,'This is a mature, pressure-free response that keeps the process moving while respecting suitability.',147),
('platinum-wealth-venture','study','closing','A client says, "I''m interested, but I don''t want to commit today." What is the best next step?','["Pressure them by warning they may miss out if they wait","Ask what they still need to feel confident, then agree on a specific follow-up step","End the conversation and move on","Submit first and let them cancel later if needed"]'::jsonb,1,'A good closing process is collaborative and specific. It reduces friction without becoming pushy.',148),
('platinum-wealth-venture','study','closing','A client says, "Send me the details and I''ll look at it." What is the best advisor response?','["Send only the illustration and hope they reply","Send a clear summary, highlight the key decision points, and schedule a follow-up discussion","Keep texting daily until they commit","Tell them the product is too complex to explain over message"]'::jsonb,1,'The advisor should make it easy for the client to review, while also creating a clear next step.',149),
('platinum-wealth-venture','study','closing','A prospect says, "I need to discuss this with my spouse." What is the best response?','["That''s okay — let''s arrange a time to go through it together so both of you can decide with the same information.","No need, you can decide on your own.","That usually just delays things.","Sign first, then explain it later."]'::jsonb,0,'This response respects the decision process and increases the chance of a better-quality follow-up.',150),
('platinum-wealth-venture','study','closing','A client says, "I''m worried this is too big a commitment." What is the best closing approach?','["Push harder on the dividend potential","Revisit whether the amount is appropriately sized and whether the case should be adjusted or deferred","Tell them commitment anxiety is normal and ignore it","Offer to change product features that do not exist"]'::jsonb,1,'A strong closer does not bulldoze resistance. They diagnose whether the hesitation is about suitability, sizing, or understanding.',151),
('platinum-wealth-venture','study','closing','A client likes PWV but is comparing it against doing nothing for now. What is the best response?','["Doing nothing is always a mistake.","Let''s compare the trade-offs clearly — liquidity, growth potential, policy benefits, and what waiting would mean for your timeline.","PWV is obviously better than waiting.","Waiting is only for indecisive people."]'::jsonb,1,'This is a strong advisory close because it helps the client make a reasoned decision instead of reacting to pressure.',152),
('platinum-wealth-venture','study','closing','A client says, "I understand the product, but I''m still not sure it''s the best fit." What is the best reply?','["Then you should just trust my recommendation.","Let''s clarify what outcome you want, what alternatives you are considering, and whether this plan truly fits better than those options.","That uncertainty will go away after you sign.","All good products feel uncertain at first."]'::jsonb,1,'This is the right way to close uncertain clients: by clarifying fit, not by forcing commitment.',153);